description:
Every create input struct requires caller to pass client_id: &str. This exposes a JMAP protocol detail (the create map key) that the library should own. A third-party caller does not know what a JMAP client ID is and should not have to generate one.

Fix: generate a ULID internally on each create call. Expose an optional override for idempotency (retry same request with same ID):

// Before: caller must generate ULID
MessageCreateInput { client_id: 'my-ulid-001', body: 'Hello', ... }

// After: generated transparently
MessageCreateInput { body: 'Hello', ... }

// After, with idempotency override:
MessageCreateInput { body: 'Hello', client_id: None, ... } // auto
MessageCreateInput { body: 'Hello', client_id: Some('my-id'), ... } // explicit

Affected structs (9): MessageCreateInput, CustomEmojiCreateInput, SpaceInviteCreateInput, SpaceBanCreateInput, SpaceCreateInput, ChatCreateDirectInput, ChatCreateGroupInput, ChatCreateChannelInput, PushSubscriptionCreateInput.

Dependency: add ulid crate (or generate via uuid). The generated client_id must be surfaced to the caller via the SetResponse created map key.
